{
  "stem": "11671.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- in 1944 when the Hungarian Jews were picked, they killed about 400,000 Jews real fast, and they did not want to take the time to tattoo you.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so we were-- the Hungarian Jews were just, just like 10,000 a day.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, they were just killing them as fast as possible.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we were just kind of waiting around there, either to be killed or to be shipped out-- I mean, for the war to end.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Not to be shipped out, but for the war to end.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they didn't want to take the time to tattoo you anymore.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we were never tattooed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "About my-- we, we never-- we used to see men soldiers, men prisoners walk by every now and then.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We always looked closely to see if we knew anybody.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People would ask about their relatives, but nobody knew anything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The only one that we saw was an aunt, [NON-ENGLISH], who was taken from Cluj, but a different time than we were.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we met there again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she was in a different barracks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But that's the only one we met.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And some school friends, but we never heard anything about our, our cousins and aunts and uncles.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We never saw them again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We never heard anything about them until after the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We, we, we-- I think we survived because we were able to support each other.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And like, like, in numbers, there's strength, you know, and just-- we would encourage each other.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Every time when one was down and real depressed and the other one would say, OK, you know, just the war will end, and just, you know, hold on, and just to, to encourage each other and support each other.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
